00:21:21.947 --> 00:21:23.865
God. why is this happening to me?

489
00:21:23.866 --> 00:21:25.867
Is that rhetorical.
or do you want an actual answer?

490
00:21:25.868 --> 00:21:27.452
I can take it.

491
00:21:27.453 --> 00:21:29.829
I think it's because some people see you

492
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:32.290
as a narcissistic asshole
with a punchable face.

493
00:21:32.291 --> 00:21:34.834
- Case in point.
- Do people see me that way?

494
00:21:34.835 --> 00:21:36.127
Some people do.

495
00:21:36.128 --> 00:21:37.963
- Do you see me that way?
- No.

496
00:21:39.632 --> 00:21:40.716
Not all the time.

497
00:21:41.592 --> 00:21:44.677
I mean. you're choosing to stay at a hotel
instead of my apartment.

498
00:21:44.678 --> 00:21:48.306
and some people
might find that perplexing.

499
00:21:48.307 --> 00:21:52.353
You have a roommate. and.
you know. moving in is a big step.

500
00:21:53.103 --> 00:21:54.604
We're having a child together.

501
00:21:54.605 --> 00:21:58.316
Okay. well. if I'm such a total bastard.
why would you even wanna be with me?

502
00:21:58.317 --> 00:22:00.860
Well. at first. mostly your face.

503
00:22:00.861 --> 00:22:03.613
But then. also your mind. and that accent.

504
00:22:03.614 --> 00:22:06.408
Seriously. it's like having sex
with Paddington Bear.

505
00:22:07.952 --> 00:22:10.203
- And that does it for me.
- Well. a wise bear

506
00:22:10.204 --> 00:22:12.247
always has a marmalade sandwich
underneath his hat.

507
00:22:12.248 --> 00:22:14.666
- What are you talking about?
- It's just what the bear says.

508
00:22:14.667 --> 00:22:16.167
Look. every human is a mixed bag.

509
00:22:16.168 --> 00:22:18.044
We all have our good qualities
and our terrible ones.

510
00:22:18.045 --> 00:22:20.129
and neuroscience tells us
our brains have plasticity.

511
00:22:20.130 --> 00:22:21.798
That means through repetition
and intention.

512
00:22:21.799 --> 00:22:23.341
we decide who we're gonna become.

513
00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:25.301
And you? I think you're at a crossroads.

514
00:22:25.302 --> 00:22:27.303
But I think you are going to step up

515
00:22:27.304 --> 00:22:29.390
and become the man
I know you're capable of being.

516
00:22:30.474 --> 00:22:33.560
- And what if I don't?
- Well. then I move on.

517
00:22:33.561 --> 00:22:35.937
There. all done. Anything else?

518
00:22:35.938 --> 00:22:38.064
- A bold lip. perhaps?
- I think I'm good.

519
00:22:38.065 --> 00:22:40.860
Coward. I'm going back to class.

520
00:22:46.073 --> 00:22:47.740
Oh.

521
00:22:47.741 --> 00:22:48.826
Huh?

522
00:22:50.911 --> 00:22:53.122
- You took it?
- Yeah. I did.

523
00:22:56.208 --> 00:22:59.378
You did the one thing I never did
to make me feel worse?

524
00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:01.839
Hmm. Okay.

525
00:23:04.508 --> 00:23:05.925
Look. I know you didn't like it

526
00:23:05.926 --> 00:23:08.261
when I called you a rock star.
but you are.

527
00:23:08.262 --> 00:23:09.721
- Please don't.
- You are.

528
00:23:09.722 --> 00:23:11.306
Get over it.

529
00:23:11.307 --> 00:23:15.269
But recently. you have been doing
some stuff that's a little loser-ish.

530
00:23:15.936 --> 00:23:18.313
I know. because I have been there.

531
00:23:18.314 --> 00:23:20.189
Lack of game recognizes lack of game.

532
00:23:20.190 --> 00:23:21.275
Ugh.

533
00:23:21.984 --> 00:23:25.446
Katie. you were right about me.
I didn't bounce back.

534
00:23:26.447 --> 00:23:30.242
And I am not resilient.
And I hope I didn't pass that down to you.

535
00:23:31.452 --> 00:23:33.245
Come on. You love this place.

536
00:23:34.204 --> 00:23:37.958
The only thing you need to do to stay
is to be brave.

537
00:23:40.210 --> 00:23:42.837
And to write a letter that says
that you're mentally ill.

538
00:23:42.838 --> 00:23:44.423
- Jesus Christ.
- Ack.

539
00:23:48.260 --> 00:23:49.761
Help me write it.

540
00:23:49.762 --> 00:23:52.555
The Elizabeth Stoddard
Student Center just opened.

541
00:23:52.556 --> 00:23:53.890
You'll notice. right behind you.

542
00:23:53.891 --> 00:23:57.560
we kept the original
brick facade from 1821.

543
00:23:57.561 --> 00:23:59.854
- Cristle said you were here.
- Thank you.

544
00:23:59.855 --> 00:24:01.230
You know. I hate this damn building.

545
00:24:01.231 --> 00:24:03.149
- Ah.
- They took a classic example

546
00:24:03.150 --> 00:24:06.444
of Neo-Gothic architecture
and slapped a greenhouse on it.

547
00:24:06.445 --> 00:24:07.403
Well. they also added

548
00:24:07.404 --> 00:24:08.571
- a smashburger place.
- Exactly.

549
00:24:08.572 --> 00:24:10.782
We're sacrificing tradition for what?

550
00:24:10.783 --> 00:24:13.493
More fat kids?
We damn sure got plenty of those.

551
00:24:13.494 --> 00:24:15.078
No. no. Not out loud.

552
00:24:15.079 --> 00:24:16.913
- Thank you.
- Okay.

553
00:24:16.914 --> 00:24:18.915
What brought all this on?

554
00:24:18.916 --> 00:24:21.042
- Rough dinner with Dean Riggs.
- Mm.

555
00:24:21.043 --> 00:24:22.628
And I had to tell him
we were cutting his budget.

556
00:24:23.504 --> 00:24:26.172
It just feels like this
is my whole job now.

557
00:24:26.173 --> 00:24:27.799
People come and ask me for things

558
00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:29.926
that they really care about.
I have to say no.

559
00:24:29.927 --> 00:24:31.970
and then they hold it against me.

560
00:24:31.971 --> 00:24:34.263
Okay. your real friends know
that this comes with the gig.

561
00:24:34.264 --> 00:24:36.392
- We're not gonna hold it against you.
- Hope so.

562
00:24:39.478 --> 00:24:41.479
I have to move <i>The Ludlow Review</i> online.

563
00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:43.898
It's part of our Green Initiative.

564
00:24:43.899 --> 00:24:45.692
Every year we print it. it just winds up

565
00:24:45.693 --> 00:24:48.152
littered all over campus
like a paper factory exploded.

566
00:24:48.153 --> 00:24:49.278
Walt. you can't do that.

567
00:24:49.279 --> 00:24:51.322
So many people are gonna be upset.

568
00:24:51.323 --> 00:24:54.659
No. The 36 students who get published
will be upset.

569
00:24:54.660 --> 00:24:56.829
Some of their 72 parents. and...

570
00:24:57.955 --> 00:24:58.956
and me.

571
00:25:01.000 --> 00:25:03.794
I read it cover to cover every year.

572
00:25:07.423 --> 00:25:09.049
I'm really sorry.

573
00:25:12.177 --> 00:25:14.721
"All of that said.
I am truly and profoundly sorry.

574
00:25:14.722 --> 00:25:16.806
My behavior was unhinged. and I..."

575
00:25:16.807 --> 00:25:19.142
- I don't love "unhinged."
- Really?

576
00:25:19.143 --> 00:25:21.185
I'm gonna use "overwhelmed."

577
00:25:21.186 --> 00:25:22.604
It's your letter.
Doesn't have to be great.

578
00:25:24.231 --> 00:25:25.732
But I love it.

579
00:25:25.733 --> 00:25:27.442
Okay. done.

580
00:25:27.443 --> 00:25:29.694
- Look at this guy.
- Mm.

581
00:25:29.695 --> 00:25:31.404
- I get to hide him. right?
- All yours.

582
00:25:31.405 --> 00:25:33.990
I'm gonna save it for when
I need a pick-me-up.

583
00:25:33.991 --> 00:25:35.783
Like. first time I see that fucker

584
00:25:35.784 --> 00:25:37.828
- pushing around a stroller.
- Mm.

585
00:25:38.954 --> 00:25:39.830
Wait. what now?

586
00:25:50.007 --> 00:25:51.841
Hi! Hi. I'm so sorry.

587
00:25:51.842 --> 00:25:54.594
- I forgot my key again.
- No problem.

588
00:25:54.595 --> 00:25:56.304
That's happening to you a lot.

589
00:25:56.305 --> 00:25:58.223
I know. I'm so mad at myself!

590
00:25:59.308 --> 00:26:00.933
<i>How do we expect the Russian government</i>

591
00:26:00.934 --> 00:26:03.978
<i>to respond to this bold move
from Downing Street?</i>

592
00:26:03.979 --> 00:26:05.980
<i>Well. it's certainly
not going to go smoothly.</i>

593
00:26:05.981 --> 00:26:07.648
<i>that's for sure.</i>

594
00:26:07.649 --> 00:26:09.651
<i>- You got her pregnant?!
- No. is that a ladle?</i>

595
00:26:14.406 --> 00:26:15.573
<i>Not now!</i>

596
00:26:15.574 --> 00:26:17.200
<i>- Mr. Bates...
- It's a big opportunity. Greg!</i>

597
00:26:17.201 --> 00:26:18.659
<i>You're live on the BBC.</i>

598
00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:19.661
<i>Ow!</i>

599
00:26:21.789 --> 00:26:24.123
- Is that Greg?
- Yes.

600
00:26:24.124 --> 00:26:25.167
Fuck him up.

601
00:26:27.628 --> 00:26:29.128
- Oh!
- Oh. my God.

602
00:26:29.129 --> 00:26:30.214
- Oh!
- Oh!

603
00:26:31.548 --> 00:26:33.300
Eli! Eli!

604
00:26:34.134 --> 00:26:36.220
Eli. you okay? You need your inhaler?

605
00:26:48.857 --> 00:26:50.024
<i>Hey there.</i>

606
00:26:50.025 --> 00:26:51.443
You got a coffee walk in you?

607
00:26:52.361 --> 00:26:53.779
Can't. I'm really busy.

608
00:27:00.744 --> 00:27:02.453
- Hey.
- Hey!

609
00:27:02.454 --> 00:27:06.082
I appreciate you putting all
this unfortunate fire business to rest.

610
00:27:06.083 --> 00:27:08.794
Oh. yeah. No problem at all.

611
00:27:09.711 --> 00:27:14.132
Say. when you were in the cold plunge.
you didn't happen to see my gun. did you?

612
00:27:14.133 --> 00:27:15.508
- I did not.
- It's fine.

613
00:27:15.509 --> 00:27:17.344
I probably left it on my dash.

614
00:27:18.345 --> 00:27:20.972
Ah! Oh! No.

615
00:27:20.973 --> 00:27:22.557
I left it at the gun range.

616
00:27:22.558 --> 00:27:24.517
Best place to leave a gun.

617
00:27:24.518 --> 00:27:25.894
They're hard to keep track of.

618
00:27:30.315 --> 00:27:32.067
I thought I'd try to be less perplexing.

619
00:27:39.158 --> 00:27:40.659
I'm funnier than people think.

620
00:27:41.994 --> 00:27:43.745
Thank you. Thank you.

621
00:27:44.872 --> 00:27:46.372
Ugh. this fucking guy.

622
00:27:46.373 --> 00:27:48.166
Hello. Mo. How are you?

623
00:27:48.167 --> 00:27:49.793
What. are you moving in?

624
00:27:52.212 --> 00:27:54.881
Well. thanks for coming to see me off.

625
00:27:54.882 --> 00:27:55.883
Yeah.

626
00:27:56.925 --> 00:27:59.552
I'm not. like.
crushed that you're leaving.

627
00:27:59.553 --> 00:28:00.846
No offense.

628
00:28:02.055 --> 00:28:04.892
But I am really glad that you came.

629
00:28:05.893 --> 00:28:07.060
Me. too.

630
00:28:08.437 --> 00:28:10.480
- I love you.
- I love you back.

631
00:28:13.275 --> 00:28:14.276
Bye. Dad.

632
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:17.029
Bye. sweetie.

633
00:28:18.530 --> 00:28:20.823
- See you Monday!
- Wait. what?

634
00:28:20.824 --> 00:28:22.451
Go. go. go!

635
00:29:25.347 --> 00:29:27.266
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

635
00:29:28.305 --> 00:30:28.362
